  "detailed_description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>If we accept that our Reality may be a Simulation, then shouldn't we accept that our simulations (games) may be somebody else's Reality?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Carceri is a fun, meta story about the Programs that run modern society. They're alive and need your help, human, because <strong>in Carceri, you aren't a Character, you are YOU, the person at your PC, reading these words.</strong> This game's world is the Programs' Reality, and you're just visiting. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/89e37e39a5e686746cdc10fc6215b96a.poster.avif?t=1758251915\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/89e37e39a5e686746cdc10fc6215b96a.webm?t=1758251915\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/89e37e39a5e686746cdc10fc6215b96a.mp4?t=1758251915\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Think of Carceri as a virtual vacation to a technicolor, living landscape; a chill, first-person narrative/exploration experience. You'll discover gorgeous, interconnected zones while platforming, talking to cute NPCs, finding secrets, and taking pictures with a heavily upgradable Camera, one that can wildly distort the world as you explore (<strong>this isn't a Photo Mode, it's you as the game's Art Director</strong>)!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Carceri is a 2-4 hour game made by a single human; a spiritual successor to <strong>ULTRAWORLD EXODUS</strong>. This is no Dark Souls, as anyone can complete the narrative portion, and there's plenty to find afterwards (like an in-game philosophy podcast...about the Simulation Hypothesis, as it relates to videogames. Don't worry, it's optional).</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Works on Steamdeck, and, buying the game gives you the 41 song original soundtrack!</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/c74db831feea7cd110b2eb30bcdd5bdc.poster.avif?t=1758251915\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/c74db831feea7cd110b2eb30bcdd5bdc.webm?t=1758251915\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/c74db831feea7cd110b2eb30bcdd5bdc.mp4?t=1758251915\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Carceri is  quietly unlike anything you've played before. It's hard to explain (and sell), but it's absolutely worth the world's most precious resource: your time.  Enjoy!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/72fc7199564673639436ac032fbd9632.poster.avif?t=1758251915\" width=616 height=346 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/72fc7199564673639436ac032fbd9632.webm?t=1758251915\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2941820/extras/72fc7199564673639436ac032fbd9632.mp4?t=1758251915\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p>",
